Class ExternalChildResourceImpl<FluentModelT,InnerModelT,ParentImplT extends ParentT,ParentT>

    public abstract class ExternalChildResourceImpl<FluentModelT,InnerModelT,ParentImplT extends ParentT,ParentT>
extends ChildResourceImpl<InnerModelT,ParentImplT,ParentT>
implements ExternalChildResource<FluentModelT,ParentT>
    Externalized child resource abstract implementation. Inorder to be eligible for an external child resource following criteria must be satisfied: 1. It's is always associated with a parent resource and has no existence without parent i.e. if you delete parent then child resource will be deleted automatically. 2. Parent will contain collection of child resources. this is not a hard requirement. 3. It's has an ID and can be created, updated, fetched and deleted independent of the parent i.e. CRUD on child resource does not require CRUD on the parent (Internal use only)
